<% content_for :title, "About & Contact — Turf Totals" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Turf Totals is a Solana-powered World Cup pick'em game. Learn who builds it, how it works on-chain, and how to reach the team." %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-10 px-2 space-y-12">
  <header>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-heading mb-2">About Turf Totals</h1>
    <p class="text-secondary text-sm">A Solana-powered sports pick&rsquo;em game for the 2026 World Cup.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">What Turf Totals is</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Turf Totals is a skill-based pick&rsquo;em game built around the 2026 FIFA World Cup.
      Each contest gives you a slate of team matchups. You pick six, each one carrying a
      <strong>Turf Score</strong> weighted by the team&rsquo;s world ranking, and your entry is scored as
      <em>goals scored &times; Turf Score</em> once the real matches are played. The highest total
      across all entrants wins the prize pool.
    </p>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Entry fees and prize pools settle on the <strong>Solana</strong> blockchain in USDC, so payouts
      are transparent and verifiable on-chain rather than sitting in an opaque custodial balance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">How it works on-chain</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>
        Entering a contest is a single <strong>SPL token transfer</strong> of your USDC entry fee
        from your own wallet to the contest&rsquo;s operator revenue account, routed through our
        audited <strong>Turf Vault</strong> program. There is no token approval, no delegate
        authority, and no &ldquo;unlimited spend&rdquo; grant &mdash; each transaction moves exactly the
        entry fee and nothing else.
      </li>
      <li>
        Your USDC stays in <strong>your own associated token account</strong> until you choose to
        enter a contest. Turf Totals never takes custody of an open-ended balance.
      </li>
      <li>
        Prize payouts are distributed from a per-contest prize-pool account and require a
        <strong>2-of-3 multisig</strong> to release &mdash; no single operator key can move prize funds.
      </li>
      <li>
        Anyone can audit the live numbers on our
        <%= link_to "Proof of Reserves", proof_of_reserves_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
        and
        <%= link_to "Smart Contract", contract_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
        pages, which read the on-chain accounts directly from your browser.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Who builds it</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Turf Totals is built and operated by McRitchie Studio, an independent software studio.
      The game, the web app, and the on-chain Turf Vault program are developed in-house. We run
      on Solana for fast, low-cost, verifiable settlement, and we use
      <%= link_to "Phantom", help_phantom_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
      and other Solana wallets for sign-in and payments.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact" class="space-y-4 scroll-mt-24">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Contact us</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Questions, support requests, or partnership inquiries? We read every message.
    </p>
    <div class="card p-6 space-y-3">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-2xl">&#9993;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="text-heading font-semibold">Email</div>
          <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">alex@turfmonster.media</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-2xl">&#9917;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="text-heading font-semibold">Help Center</div>
          <%= link_to "How to play, Phantom wallet, and glossary", help_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-2xl">&#128221;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="text-heading font-semibold">Legal</div>
          <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
          <span class="text-secondary">&middot;</span>
          <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3 text-sm text-secondary border-t border-subtle pt-6">
    <p>
      Turf Totals is a game of skill. Please play responsibly and only in jurisdictions where
      skill-based contests are permitted. You must be of legal age in your jurisdiction to enter.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
